Some of these new type cars are equipped with domes from which the passenger can obtain an entirely new perspective as he watches the country- side from a sun-glass-enclosed posi- tion at the top of the car.

In sleeping cars, the trend is toward the small type room for single occu- pancy, but here, “too, the range in improvements runs from individual berths to drawing rooms. For instance, a typical drawing room on a new car offers spacious accommodations for three passengers and includes a pri- vate, fully—enclosed lavatory. Along one wall is a three-place sofa with adjustable arm rests. There are also two movable lounge chairs, and light— ing and temperature controls are all on one convenient panel.
